		{
			"objects": {
				"Text18": {
					"type": "text",
					"text": "Introduction and setup",
					"top": 41,
					"left": 23,
					"width": 314,
					"height": 28,
					"class": "title"
				},
				"Rectangle1": {
					"type": "rectangle",
					"top": 96,
					"left": 23,
					"width": 239,
					"height": 615,
					"borderRadius": 10,
					"stroke": "#EBEBEB",
					"class": "background"
				},
				"Text13": {
					"type": "text",
					"text": "This demo will teach you how to use 4D AI Kit to implement model tool calling.\r\rIt comes with a pre-generated database with pre-generateed embeddings.\r\rRreview the table on the right and setup your AI providers: you will need at least 1 embedding model and 1 reasoning model..\r\rVocabulary:\rreasoning models are used by generative AI. They are used in this demo to generate persons in database, but also to interact.\r\rEmbedding models are used to compute embeddings.\r\rEmbedding is the process that transforms data (often text) into a vector. The resulting vector is also called an embedding.\r\rTools calling: several recent reasoning models now support tool calling. Based on your prompt and on tools that you declare, the model can decide to call a tool and interpret its result before answering.",
					"top": 106,
					"left": 32,
					"width": 219,
					"height": 605,
					"class": "description"
				},
				"Text5": {
					"type": "text",
					"text": "AI providers list",
					"top": 92,
					"left": 283,
					"width": 955,
					"height": 22,
					"class": "subtitle"
				},
				"ProvidersListBox": {
					"type": "listbox",
					"left": 283,
					"top": 121,
					"width": 1015,
					"height": 188,
					"events": [
						"onClick",
